text: Mohammed Abdullah Al-Ajmi is a member of the Kuwaiti National Assembly, representing the fifth district. Born in 1971, Al-Ajmi obtained a PhD in management from Yarmouk University in Jordan and worked as a professor before being elected to the National Assembly in 2008. Al-Ajmi is considered an Independent deputy. He is a member of the Ajman tribe.Arab Times MP Profile ==References== Category:Kuwaiti politicians Category:Members of the National Assembly of Kuwait Category:Living people Category:1971 births Category:Yarmouk University alumni
